net.ashwork.functionality.operator

Interface Operator2<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the operands and result of the operator
    All Superinterfaces:
    net.ashwork.functionality.partial.Arity, net.ashwork.functionality.Function2<T,T,T>, net.ashwork.functionality.FunctionN<T>, OperatorN<T>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.ResultChainable<T>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.ResultChainableResult<T>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.Variant<java.util.function.BiFunction<T,T,T>>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Operator2<T>
extends OperatorN<T>, net.ashwork.functionality.Function2<T,T,T>
    Represents an operation that accepts two operands and produces a result of the same type as its operands. This is the two-arity specialization of OperatorN. This is a specialization of Function2 where the operands and result are of the same type.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is Function2.apply(Object, Object).

    Since:
    1.0.0

    OperatorN, Function2
